events.description: The release of the number of job quits in the US for December 2025, showing a 6-month high.

facts.fact_text: The number of job quits in the US rose to 3.204 million in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: The number of job quits in the US rose slightly to 3.204 million in December 2025 from the upwardly revised 3.193 million in November

facts.fact_text: The US quits rate stood at 2% in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: The quits rate, a metric that measures voluntary job leavers as a proportion of total employment, stood at 2% in December, matching November's reading.

facts.fact_text: Job quits in retail trade increased by 87,000.

evidences.evidence_text: Quits rose primarily in retail trade (+87,000)

facts.fact_text: Job quits in professional and business services decreased by 151,000.

evidences.evidence_text: but fell in professional and business services (-151,000)

claims.claim_text: The December 2025 job quits figure was the highest reading in six months.

evidences.evidence_text: It was the highest reading in six months.

evidence.evidence_text: The quits rate, a metric that measures voluntary job leavers as a proportion of total employment, stood at 2% in December
Quits rose primarily in retail trade (+87,000)
but fell in professional and business services (-151,000)
